0/http://www.toonopedia.com/capmarv1.htm Archived] from the original on April 9, 2012.\n* {{DCDP|William Batson (New Earth)|Captain Marvel}}\n* {{Dcauw|Captain Marvel}}\n\n{{Timeline\n|before= \u2190 ''Whiz Comics'' series was debuted by Fawcett Comics. See [[Whiz Comics]] for more info and the previous timeline.\n|title= [[Timeline of DC Comics]] ([[Timeline of DC Comics (1940s)|1940s]])\n|years= February 1940 (See also: [[Shazam (wizard)]], [[Seven Deadly Enemies of Man]] and [[Doctor Sivana]])\n|after = The first Ibis the Invincible was debuted by Tad Williams and Phil Winslade. See [[Ibis the Invincible]] for more info and next timeline. \u2192\n}}\n{{Shazam|state=expanded}}\n{{Otto Binder}}\n{{Justice League}}\n{{Justice Society of America}}\n{{Justice League International}}\n{{All-Star Squadron}}\n{{Justice League characters}}\n{{GoldenAge}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Captain Marvel (Dc Comics)}}\n[[Category:1939 comics debuts]]\n[[Category:1972 comics debuts]]\n[[Category:American comics characters]]\n[[Category:Captain Marvel (DC Comics)| ]]\n[[Category:Characters created by C. C. Beck]]\n[[Category:Characters created by Bill Parker (comics)]]\n[[Category:Comics characters introduced in 1939]]\n[[Category:DC Comics American superheroes]]\n[[Category:DC Comics adapted into films]]\n[[Category:DC Comics characters who can move at superhuman speeds]]\n[[Category:DC Comics characters with accelerated healing]]\n[[Category:DC Comics characters with superhuman strength]]\n[[Category:Fictional characters granted magic or power through dealings]]\n[[Category:DC Comics child superheroes]]\n[[Category:DC Comics titles]]\n[[Category:Fawcett Comics titles]]\n[[Category:Fictional characters with electric or magnetic abilities]]\n[[Category:Fictional characters with precognition]]\n[[Category:Fictional orphans]]\n[[Category:Fictional radio personalities]]\n[[Category:Fictional twins]]\n[[Category:Film serial characters]]\n[[Category:Golden Age superheroes]]\n