 British Imperialism and Kenyatta, 1963\u20131978  |publisher=Palgrave Macmillan |location=London |isbn=978-3319509648 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite book |last=Molony |first=Thomas |title=Nyerere: The Early Years |year=2014 |location=Woodbridge, Suffolk |publisher=Boydell and Brewer |isbn=978-1847010902 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite article |first=Herbert T. |last=Neve |title=The Political Life of Julius K. Nyerere in Religious Perspective |journal=Africa Today |volume=23 |number=4 |year=1976 |pages=29\u201345 |jstor=4185638 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite book |last=Pratt |first=Cranford |year=1976 |title=The Critical Phase in Tanzania 1945\u20131968: Nyerere and the Emergence of a Socialist Strategy |url=https://archive.org/details/criticalphaseint0000prat |url-access=registration |publisher=Cambridge University Press |location=Cambridge |isbn=978-0-521-20824-6 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite article |first=Cranford |last=Pratt |year=2000 |title=Julius Nyerere: The Ethical Foundation of his Legacy |journal=The Round Table |volume=89 |pages=365\u2013374 |doi=10.1080/00358530050083442 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite article |first=George |last=Roberts |year=2014 |title=The Uganda\u2013Tanzania War, the Fall of Idi Amin, and the Failure of African Diplomacy, 1978\u20131979 |journal=Journal of Eastern African Studies |volume=8 |issue=4 |pages=692\u2013709 |doi=10.1080/17531055.2014.946236 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite article |first=Issa G. |last=Shivji |year=2012 |title=Nationalism and Pan-Africanism: Decisive Moments in Nyerere's Intellectual and Political Thought |journal=Review of African Political Economy |volume=39 |pages=103\u2013116 |doi=10.1080/03056244.2012.662387 |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite book |first=William Edgett |last=Smith |title=Nyerere of Tanzania |publisher=Victor Gollanz |location=London |year=1973 |isbn=9780575015104  |ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite book |last=Mwakikagile |first=Godfrey |title=Life Under Nyerere |edition=second |location=Dar Es Salaam and Pretoria |publisher=New Africa Press |year=2006 |isbn=978-0980258721 |ref=harv}}\n\n{{Refend}}\n\n===Further reading===\n{{Refbegin|33em|indent=yes}}\n\n: {{cite article |last=Becker |first=Felicitas |title=Remembering Nyerere: Political Rhetoric and Dissent in Contemporary Tanzania |journal=African Affairs |volume=112 |pages=238\u2013261 |doi=10.1093/afraf/adt019 |ref=}}\n\n: {{cite article |last=Lal |first=Priya |title=African Socialism and the Limits of Global Familyhood: Tanzania and the New International Economic Order in Sub-Saharan Africa |journal=Humanity: An International Journal of Human Rights, Humanitarianism, and Development |volume=6 |number=1 |year=2015 |pages=17\u201331 |ref=}}\n\n: {{cite book |last=Lal |first=Priya |year=2015 |title=African Socialism in Postcolonial Tanzania: Between the Village and the World |location=Cambridge |publisher=Cambridge University Press |isbn=978-1107104525 |ref=}}\n\n: {{cite article |last1=Mesaki |first1=Simeon |first2=Mrisho |last2=Malipula |title=Julius Nyerere's Influence and Legacy: From a Proponent of Familyhood to a Candidate for Sainthood |journal=International Journal of Sociology and Anthropology |volume=3 |issue=3 |pages=93\u2013100 |year=2011 |ref=}}\n\n: {{cite article |last=Metz |first=Steven |title=In Lieu of Orthodoxy: The Socialist Theories of Nkrumah and Nyerere |journal=The Journal of Modern African Studies |volume=20 |issue=3 |year=1982 |pages=377\u2013392 |ref=}}\n\n: {{cite article |last=Mhina |first=Mary Ann |year=2014 |title=The Poetry of an Orphaned Nation: Newspaper Poetry and the Death of Nyerere |journal=Journal of Eastern African Studies |volume=8 |issue=3 |pages=497\u2013514 |doi=10.1080/17531055.2014.917857 |ref=}}\n\n: {{cite article |first=Derek C. |last=Mulenga |year=2001 |title=Mwalimu Julius Nyerere: A Critical Review of his Contributions to Adult Education and Postcolonialism |journal=International Journal of Lifelong Education |volume=20 |issue=6 |pages=446\u2013470 |doi=10.1080/02601370110088436 |ref=}}\n\n: {{cite article