{"title_page": "List of Chinese soups", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n<!-- Please edit below this line --> \n[[File:Pho-style noodle soup (cropped).jpg|thumb|[[Beef noodle soup]]]]\n\nThis is a '''list of notable Chinese soups'''. [[Chinese cuisine]] includes styles originating from the diverse regions of China, as well as from Chinese people in other parts of the world. Many Chinese soups are [[noodle]]-based. By 2000 BCE, wheat had arrived in China from western Asia. These grains were typically served as warm [[noodle soup]]s instead of baked into bread as in Europe. [[Chinese noodles]] are used in the preparation of some Chinese soups.\n\n==Chinese soups==\n{{dynamic list}}\n* ''[[Bak kut teh]]\n* ''[[Banmian]]''\n* [[Bat Soup]] <ref>{{cite book | last=Chang | first=D. | last2=Ling | first2=L. | title=Lucky Rice: Stories and Recipes from Night Markets, Feasts, and Family Tables | publisher=Potter/TenSpeed/Harmony | year=2016 | isbn=978-0-8041-8669-8 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=O8cOCAAAQBAJ&pg=PT50 | accessdate=January 3, 2017 | page=50}}</ref>\n\n* [[Beef noodle soup]] <ref>{{cite book | last=Chang | first=D. | last2=Ling | first2=L. | title=Lucky Rice: Stories and Recipes from Night Markets, Feasts, and Family Tables | publisher=Potter/TenSpeed/Harmony | year=2016 | isbn=978-0-8041-8669-8 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=O8cOCAAAQBAJ&pg=PT50 | accessdate=January 3, 2017 | page=50}}</ref>\n* [[Black sesame soup]] \n* Boiled mutton soup\n* [[Buddha Jumps Over the Wall]] \n* [[Cantonese seafood soup]] \n* [[Carp|Carp soup]] <ref>{{cite book | last=Newman | first=J.M. | title=Food Culture in China | publisher=Greenwood Press | series=Food culture around the world | year=2004 | isbn=978-0-313-32581-6 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Jt6u8RZw51cC&pg=PA25 | accessdate=January 3, 2017 | pages=25\u201326}}</ref>\n* [[Chicken and duck blood soup]] \n* [[Chicken soup]] \u2013 Many Chinese soups are based on [[chicken broth]]. Typical Chinese chicken soup is made from old hens and is seasoned with [[ginger]], [[scallion]]s, [[black pepper]], [[soy sauce]], [[rice wine]] and [[sesame oil]].\n* [[Corn crab soup]] \n* [[Crossing the bridge noodles]]\n* [[Duck blood and vermicelli soup]] \n* [[Edible bird's nest]] \n* [[Egg drop soup]] <ref>{{cite book | last=Anderson | first=H.A. | title=Breakfast: A History | publisher=AltaMira Press | series=The Meals Series | year=2013 | isbn=978-0-7591-2165-2 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5LghYCqDJw8C&pg=PA62 | accessdate=January 3, 2017 | page=62}}</ref>\n* ''[[Egg tong sui]]''\n* [[Brassica juncea|Fish and mustard leaf soup]] \n* [[Fish head|Fish head soup]] \n* ''[[Geng (dish)|Geng]]''\n* Chinese herbal soups  \u2013 homemade remedies with [[herb]]s or adaptogens (a well-known example is ginseng) to help heal specific health concerns.\n* [[Hot and sour soup]] \n* ''[[Hulatang]]''\n* ''[[Walnut soup#By country|Hup Tul Woo]]'' \u2013 a sweet walnut soup\n* ''[[Jiuniang]]''\n* [[Lettuce soup]] \n* [[Liver soup]] \n* [[Lotus seed#Chinese medicinal foods|Lotus seed]] and pork tripe soup \n* [[Lung fung soup]] <ref>{{cite book | last=Philpott | first=D. | title=The World of Wine and Food: A Guide to Varieties, Tastes, History, and Pairings | publisher=Rowman & Littlefield Publishers | year=2016 | isbn=978-1-4422-6804-3 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3dIbDQAAQBAJ&pg=PA302 | accessdate=January 3, 2017 | page=302}}</ref>\n* [[Mung bean]] soup\n* [[Noodle soup]]\n* ''[[Nam ngiao]]''\n* [[Nangchang Jar soup]]\n* [[Oxtail soup]] \n* [[Patriotic soup]] \u2013 developed during the [[Mongol conquest of the Song dynasty]] and named by [[Emperor Bing of Song]]. It is part of [[Teochew cuisine]] and is simple to prepare. Its main ingredients are [[leaf vegetable]], broth, and edible mushrooms.\n* [[Pig's organ soup]] \n* [[Pigeon|Pigeon soup]]\n* [[Pork blood soup]]\n* [[Red bean soup]] \n* [[Sago soup]] \n* [[Shark fin soup]] <ref>{{cite book | last=Branch | first=Australia. Fisheries | title=Australian Fisheries Newsletter | issue=v. 26 | year=1967 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RxsiAQAAIAAJ | accessdate=January 3, 2017|page=9}}</ref>\n* [[Silkie#In cuisine|Silkie soup]] \u2013 Also known as ''Black chicken soup'' \n* Stewed chicken soup\n* [[Sweet potato soup]] \n* ''[[Tian mo]]''\n* [[Tomato and egg soup]] \n* ''[[Tong sui]]''\n* [[Turtle soup]] \u2013 In countries such as [[Singapore]] with large [[Chinese people|Chinese]] populations, turtle soup is a Chinese delicacy.\n* [[Melon soup#Winter melon soup|Winter melon spare rib soup]] \n* [[Wonton noodles|Wonton noodle]]\n* ''[[Xidoufen]]''\n* ''[[Yong Tau Foo]]''\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery class=\"center\" caption=\"Chinese soups\" widths=\"195px\" heights=\"150px\">\nFile:Buddha soup2.jpg|[[Buddha Jumps Over the Wall]]\nFile:Chinese-style geng with meat, fish cakes, and squid.jpg|A bowl of meat-based ''[[Geng (dish)|geng]]''\nFile:Hulatang.png|''[[Hulatang]]''\nFile:Chinese cuisine-Shark fin soup-01.jpg|[[Shark fin soup]]\nFile:Song dynasty's 'patriotic soup' (prepared in Clovis California) \u5b8b\u671d\u7684\u201c\u8b77\u570b\u83dc\u201d\uff08\u5728\u52a0\u5229\u798f\u5c3c\u4e9e\u514b\u6d1b\u7dad\u65af\u5e02\u88fd\u5099\uff09(2)\u3002.jpg|[[Song dynasty]]'s \"[[patriotic soup]]\"\nFile:BlacksesameSoup.jpg|[[Black sesame soup]]\nFile:Guo Qiao Mi Xian.jpg|[[Crossing the bridge noodles]]\nFile:Eggtongsui.jpg|[[Egg tong sui]]\nFile:Hup Tul Woo - walnut dessert soup.jpg|''Hup Tul Woo'', a Chinese [[walnut soup]]\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n{{portal|Food|China|Lists}}\n* [[Asian soup]]\n* [[Chinese spoon]]\n* [[List of Chinese desserts]]\n* [[List of Chinese dishes]]\n* [[List of Chinese sauces]]\n* [[List of soups]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Commons category-inline|Soups and stews of China}}\n\n{{-}}\n{{Lists of prepared foods |state = collapsed }}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Chinese soups}}\n[[Category:Chinese soups|*]